==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Iceland moss
<hw>Ice"land moss`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A kind of
lichen (<spn>Cetraria Icelandica</spn>) found from the Arctic regions to
the North Temperate zone. It furnishes a nutritious jelly and other
forms of food, and is used in pulmonary complaints as a
demulcent.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Iceland spar</ent>⟦br⟧
